data.chText: 生涯；职业
data.enText: the series of jobs that a person has in a particular area of work, usually involving more responsibility as time passes

data.chText: 从政生涯
data.enText: a career in politics

data.chText: 教学生涯
data.enText: a teaching career

data.chText: 是什么驱使你选择兽医这门职业的？
data.enText: What made you decide on a career as a vet?

data.chText: 她一直专心致志于她的本职工作。
data.enText: She has been concentrating on her career.

data.chText: 改换职业
data.enText: a change of career

data.chText: 那将是事业发展上明智的一步。
data.enText: That will be a good career move (= something that will help your career).

data.chText: 职业军人、外交人员等
data.enText: a career soldier/diplomat , etc. (= a professional one)

data.chText: 指导选择职业的顾问 / 官员
data.enText: a careers adviser/officer (= a person whose job is to give people advice and information about jobs)

data.chText: 经历；事业
data.enText: the period of time that you spend in your life working or doing a particular thing

data.chText: 她以当英语教师开始了她的职业生涯。
data.enText: She started her career as an English teacher.

data.chText: 他正处于他网球事业的巅峰时期。
data.enText: He is playing the best tennis of his career.

data.chText: 我的学业成绩并不很出色。
data.enText: My school career was not very impressive.

data.chText: （尤指失控地）猛冲，疾驰，飞奔
data.enText: to move forward very quickly, especially in an uncontrolled way

data.chText: 那辆车横冲过马路，撞上了一个骑自行车的人。
data.enText: The vehicle careered across the road and hit a cyclist.

data.text: work ♦ employment ♦ career ♦ profession ♦ occupation ♦ trade

data.chText: 以上各词均指有报酬的工作，尤指长期从事的职业。
data.enText: These are all words for the work that sb does in return for payment, especially over a long period of time.
work

data.chText: 指工作、职业：
data.enText: the job that sb does, especially in order to earn money

data.chText: 目前很难找到工作。
data.enText: It's very difficult to find work at the moment.
employment

data.chText: 指工作、职业、受雇、就业：
data.enText: ( rather formal ) work, especially when it is done to earn money; the state of being employed or the situation in which people have work

data.chText: 这儿只有一半的人有拿工资的工作。
data.enText: Only half the people here are in paid employment.
career

data.chText: 指生涯、职业：
data.enText: the job or series of jobs that sb has in a particular area of work, usually involving more responsibility as time passes

data.chText: 他在外交部有过一段光辉的事业。
data.enText: He had a very distinguished career in the Foreign Office.
profession

data.chText: 指需要专门技能（尤其是较高教育水平）的职业、专业：
data.enText: a type of job that needs special training or skill, especially one that needs a high level of education

data.chText: 他希望能从事医务工作。
data.enText: He hopes to enter the medical profession.

data.chText: the profession统称某专业的人、同行、同业：
data.enText: The profession is all the people who work in a particular profession.

data.chText: 法律界
data.enText: the legal profession

data.chText: the professions统称需要较高教育水平的传统职业，如医生、律师等。
data.enText: The professions are the traditional jobs that need a high level of education and training, such as being a doctor or lawyer.
occupation

data.chText: 指工作、职业：
data.enText: ( rather formal ) a job or profession

data.chText: 请写明姓名、年龄和职业。
data.enText: Please state your name, age, and occupation.
trade

data.chText: 指行业，尤指手工职业、手艺、行当：
data.enText: a job, especially one that involves working with your hands and requires special training and skills

data.chText: 木工是需要纯熟技巧的职业。
data.enText: Carpentry is a highly skilled trade.
in/out of work/employment
(a) full-time/part-time work/employment/career/profession/occupation
permanent/temporary work/employment
(a) well-paid/low-paid work/employment/profession/occupation
(a) paid/salaried/freelance/voluntary work/employment/occupation
(a/an/the) medical/legal/acting/teaching work/career/profession
to look for/seek/find work/employment/a career/an occupation
to get/obtain/give sb/offer sb/create/generate/provide work/employment

ex.chText: 很多学生打算投身法律行业。
ex.enText: Many students have the intention of joining the legal profession.
She is a nurse by profession.

synonyms.bx: 指需要经过专业培训的职业，尤指需要较高的受教育水平的职业。

ex.chText: 他找工作时首先关注的是职业前景。
ex.enText: His first concern while looking for a job is career prospects.

ex.chText: 她为了照顾家庭而牺牲了很有前途的事业。
ex.enText: She sacrificed a promising career to take care of her family.

synonyms.bx: 指从事的职业或希望毕生从事的事业。

ex.chText: 请把你的职业写在下面的方框内。
ex.enText: Please state your occupation in the box below.

ex.chText: 没有技术含量的体力工作通常挣钱不多。
ex.enText: Unskilled manual occupations usually don't earn much.

synonyms.bx: 泛指任何一种工作，通常不用来谈论自己的职业，多用于表格填写或正式书面语中。

tips.tip: 不要用 occupation 一词来谈论自己的职业，如可以说：I'm a teacher.（我是老师。）但不能说：My occupation is a teacher.

ex.chText: 他认为当作家是他真正的使命。
ex.enText: He believed that to be a writer was his true vocation.

ex.chText: 那姑娘入错行了，她本该当演员。
ex.enText: The girl missed her vocation - she should have been an actress.

synonyms.bx: 指某人认为特别适合自己的工作。

tr: the general progression of your working or professional life
example: the general had had a distinguished career
he had a long career in the law

tr: the particular occupation for which you are trained

example: The cars careered down the road
The mob careered through the streets

value.def: A career is the job or profession that someone does for a long period of their life.

example.ex: She is now concentrating on a career as a fashion designer...
example.tran: 她目前正专注于服装设计师的工作。

example.ex: Dennis had recently begun a successful career conducting opera.
example.tran: 丹尼斯最近开始从事歌剧指挥的工作,并且非常成功。

value.def: Your career is the part of your life that you spend working.

example.ex: During his career, he wrote more than fifty plays...
example.tran: 在他的创作生涯中,他写下了50多部剧本。

example.ex: She began her career as a teacher.
example.tran: 她开始了自己的教师生涯。

value.def: Careers advice or guidance in British English, or career advice or guidance in American English, consists of information about different jobs and help with deciding what kind of job you want to do.

example.ex: She received very little careers guidance when young...
example.tran: 她年轻时基本没有接受过就业指导。

example.ex: Get hold of the company list from your careers advisory service.
example.tran: 到就业指导处领取企业名录。

value.def: If a person or vehicle careers somewhere, they move fast and in an uncontrolled way.

example.ex: His car careered into a river...
He went careering off down the track.
example.tran: 他控制不住，冲出了赛道。
